==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misdo
<hw>Mis*do"</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧s*d⟦oomac⟧")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Misdid</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Misdone</conjf> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧s*d⟦ucr⟧n")</pr>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Misdoing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>misd⟦omac⟧n</ets>. See <er>Do</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To do wrongly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Afford me place to show what recompense⟦br⟧
Towards thee I intend for what I have <qex>misdone</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To do wrong to; to illtreat.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misdo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Misdo
<hw>Mis*do"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To do wrong; to commit a
fault.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have <qex>misdone</qex>, and I endure the smart.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misdoer</ent>⟦br⟧
